pageContext.claim: “If we make a car and sell it into China, they charge us a 25 percent tax. That's what it is. Twenty-five percent.”
pageContext.analysis: When Trump said this, China had announced it was cutting the 25 percent tariff to 15 percent as of July 1. General Motors sells more cars in China (3.9 million) than in the US (3 million) and saw its China business grow 13 percent in 2016.
